                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I-2 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Māryām Mariham ʾǝmmu la-ʾIyasus Krǝstos kahāli ... "O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty ..." (<locus target="13ra">13ra</locus>) (cp. ChRep n<locus target="373">373</locus>)</note>
                     <note>- salām laki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām dǝngǝl ʾǝmma madḫǝn wa-ʾǝmma bǝrhān ... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Virgin Mary, Mother of the Saviour and Mother of the Light ..." (<locus target="13ra">13ra-</locus>vb).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>The miracles of Texts I-1b, II and III are numbered (the numeration continues throughout these texts).</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>One miracle of Text I-1b (numbered as 28) is followed by a hymn:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä Māryām dǝngǝl walatta ʾAron  liqa kāhǝnāt... "O my Lady, Virgin Mary, daughter of Aaron the High Priest…" (<locus target="42va">42va</locus>)</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-5 comprises 19 strophes which are strophes 1-10 (<locus from="17va" to="24va">17va-24va</locus>), 12-14 (<locus from="29va" to="31rb">29va-31rb</locus>), 24-27 (<locus from="36rb" to="40rb">36rb-40rb</locus>) and 29-30 (42va, 44ra) according to GrohHymn pp. 336-51.</note>
                  </msItem>
